TestMethod.Description: Client implementations MUST always send the correct version number in PreMasterSecret. If ClientHello.client_version is TLS 1.1 or higher, server implementations MUST check the version number as described in the note below. [...]In any case, a TLS server MUST NOT generate an alert if processing an RSA-encrypted premaster secret message fails, or the version number is not as expected.  Instead, it MUST continue the handshake with a randomly generated premaster secret.
